{
    "id": "electronics/basic-circuit",
    "title": "Build a basic LED circuit",
    "description": "Wire a 5 mm LED and 220 Ω resistor on a breadboard to learn basic circuits.",
    "image": "/assets/quests/electronics_basic_led_breadboard_circuit.jpg",
    "npc": "/assets/npc/orion.jpg",
    "start": "start",
    "dialogue": [
        {
            "id": "start",
            "text": "Orion here. We are building a safe LED test circuit, not speed-running a spark show. Keep the 5 V supply unplugged, confirm your bench is dry, and pick a wiring strategy.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials",
                    "text": "Use the power-rail layout (faster for future edits)."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials-alt",
                    "text": "Use a compact single-row layout (good for tiny builds)."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "materials",
            "text": "Power-rail plan: collect a breadboard, two jumper wires, one 5 mm LED, one 220 Ω resistor, a resistor color chart, and a 5 V supply. Verify resistor bands before any power-on check.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "assemble",
                    "text": "Parts gathered. Start assembly.",
                    "process": "verify-resistor-color-code",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066",
                            "count": 2
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "48cf736e-184c-4bd1-b9b0-15b7e9721646",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "037e6065-68a7-4ad1-9b0b-7778ecfe0662",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "bf3d2784-d48d-4b12-b12a-75f563b5dc88",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "828d6c3b-66a5-4064-b221-97630274502b",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "materials-alt",
            "text": "Compact plan: same parts, but keep the LED and resistor in adjacent rows so polarity checks are obvious. Verify the 220 Ω code first, then wire with power disconnected.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "assemble",
                    "text": "Compact layout staged.",
                    "process": "verify-resistor-color-code",
                    "requiresItems": [
                        {
                            "id": "d1105b87-8185-4a30-ba55-406384be169f",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "3cd82744-d2aa-414e-9f03-80024b624066",
                            "count": 2
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "48cf736e-184c-4bd1-b9b0-15b7e9721646",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "037e6065-68a7-4ad1-9b0b-7778ecfe0662",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "bf3d2784-d48d-4b12-b12a-75f563b5dc88",
                            "count": 1
                        },
                        {
                            "id": "828d6c3b-66a5-4064-b221-97630274502b",
                            "count": 1
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "assemble",
            "text": "Wire LED long leg (anode) through the resistor to +5 V, short leg to ground. Re-check polarity, verify no bare jumper strands are touching, then connect power for a brief test.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "verify",
                    "text": "LED lit immediately."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "troubleshoot",
                    "text": "LED stayed dark or flickered."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "troubleshoot",
            "text": "Troubleshooting loop: unplug power first. Confirm LED orientation, resistor placement in series (not parallel bypass), and fully seated jumpers. If anything warms unexpectedly, stop and rebuild before retrying.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "assemble",
                    "text": "Issues fixed. Re-test safely."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "materials",
                    "text": "I need to re-check parts and resistor value."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "verify",
            "text": "Great. Hold test for 30 seconds; brightness should stay steady with no smell or heat at the resistor. If unstable, drop back to troubleshooting instead of forcing a finish.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "finish",
                    "text": "Stable output confirmed."
                },
                {
                    "type": "goto",
                    "goto": "troubleshoot",
                    "text": "Brightness drifted. I will debug it."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "id": "finish",
            "text": "Nice build. Disconnect the 5 V supply before touching the breadboard and log your final layout so future quests can reuse it.",
            "options": [
                {
                    "type": "finish",
                    "text": "Circuit verified."
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
